- In the criminal
justice system,

00:08.008 --> 00:09.009
sexually-based offenses

00:09.043 --> 00:11.812
are considered
especially heinous.

00:11.845 --> 00:14.248
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:14.282 --> 00:16.150
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:16.184 --> 00:17.451
are members of an elite squad

00:17.485 --> 00:19.520
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:19.553 --> 00:22.490
These are their stories.

00:22.523 --> 00:23.424
- Maybe we should set up

00:23.457 --> 00:25.359
a few more meetings
with the consultant.

00:25.393 --> 00:27.261
- We're fine
- Oh, I just found out

00:27.295 --> 00:29.130
that Matthew Sun
is on the board at Penn--

00:29.163 --> 00:31.299
- We're running late.
- Okay. All right.

00:31.332 --> 00:33.134
Oh, honey? Honey?
Just remember, okay?

00:33.167 --> 00:34.602
It's supposed to be
a conversation, you know?

00:34.635 --> 00:36.437
Just avoid yes or no answers.

00:36.470 --> 00:37.605
- Okay, Mom, I know.
- You look good.

00:37.638 --> 00:39.140
- I'll call you when
we get to Boston, okay?

00:39.173 --> 00:40.374
- Okay. All right.
Oh!

00:40.408 --> 00:43.577
Don't forget to mention your
three-week seminar in Nairobi.

00:43.611 --> 00:44.612
- Thank you.

00:49.317 --> 00:52.320
[phone buzzing]

00:54.722 --> 00:57.291
- Hey.

00:57.325 --> 00:59.193
Great.

00:59.227 --> 01:01.295
Yeah, I'll see you soon.

01:02.296 --> 01:04.465
[dark music]

01:04.498 --> 01:07.501
[both breathing heavily]

01:10.504 --> 01:11.705
- [moans]

01:11.739 --> 01:14.175
[both breathing heavily]

01:14.208 --> 01:16.277
*

01:16.310 --> 01:20.581
- Laura, are you sure
you want to have sex?

01:20.614 --> 01:21.715
- Absolutely.

01:21.749 --> 01:25.186
Why the hell do you think
we're here?

01:25.219 --> 01:27.255
[both moaning]

01:27.288 --> 01:31.659
*

01:31.692 --> 01:34.662
[water faucet running]

01:34.695 --> 01:41.702
*

01:46.507 --> 01:48.276
- All right, thank you.
- Hi.

01:48.309 --> 01:51.212
- Hey, the victim's name
is Laura Collett.

01:51.245 --> 01:52.346
She's on her way
to the hospital.

01:52.380 --> 01:54.348
It looks like an overdose,
but no note.

01:54.382 --> 01:55.583
- Who found her?
- Maintenance.

01:55.616 --> 01:57.651
2:00 a.m.
Tub started overflowing,

01:57.685 --> 01:59.320
leaking water
into the room below.

01:59.353 --> 02:00.921
- Did she check in alone?
- Well, we're not sure.

02:00.954 --> 02:02.390
We're trying to pull video
at the moment,

02:02.423 --> 02:04.258
but, I mean,
the room is in her name.

02:04.292 --> 02:05.626
She charged it on her AMEX.

02:05.659 --> 02:09.397
- Key card?
- Last used at 9:56 p.m.

02:09.430 --> 02:12.233
- Any witnesses on the floor?
- No, nobody heard a peep.

02:12.266 --> 02:14.235
- Oh, looks romantic.

02:14.268 --> 02:15.703
Flowers, a bottle of Brunello.
- Yeah.

02:15.736 --> 02:17.605
CSU's gonna check that
for narcotics.

02:17.638 --> 02:19.273
- You said there was
an outcry witness, right?

02:19.307 --> 02:20.741
- Yeah, the suspect via text.

02:20.774 --> 02:22.643
- Okay, you got a name?
- No.

02:22.676 --> 02:24.378
I called the number
a few times.

02:24.412 --> 02:26.280
No answer, no voicemail.

02:26.314 --> 02:30.484
Laura's last text was
11:56 last night.

02:30.518 --> 02:31.652
*

02:31.685 --> 02:33.387
- "You raped me.
Burn in hell."

02:33.421 --> 02:36.190
Okay, clear and concise.
- Not exactly.

02:36.224 --> 02:39.760
She sent another text to the
same guy ten minutes earlier.

02:39.793 --> 02:43.264
- "Incredible night.
Just gonna say it.

02:43.297 --> 02:44.698
Best sex ever."

02:44.732 --> 02:47.668
So, in ten minutes
she goes from "best sex ever"

02:47.701 --> 02:49.270
to "you raped me?"

02:49.303 --> 02:51.239
How the hell
does that happen?

02:51.272 --> 02:54.275
*

02:56.310 --> 02:59.280
[dramatic music]

03:43.524 --> 03:43.657
.

03:43.691 --> 03:44.392
- Hey.
The vic's at the hospital.

03:45.459 --> 03:46.427
She's still unresponsive.

03:46.460 --> 03:48.696
Nearly lethal dose of
alcohol and diazepam.

03:48.729 --> 03:50.864
- Doctor says
it's looking 50/50.

03:50.898 --> 03:52.433
- Any other drugs
in her system?

03:52.466 --> 03:54.502
- No, and the doctor did
a full tox panel.

03:54.535 --> 03:55.903
No Rohypnol or other
date rape drugs.

03:55.936 --> 03:57.505
- Okay, so the victim has sex,

03:57.538 --> 03:59.039
and then has a change of heart
after the fact.

03:59.072 --> 04:01.542
- She goes from best sex ever
to rape in ten minutes.

04:01.575 --> 04:02.610
That's a pretty
big change of heart.

04:02.643 --> 04:03.811
- Ten minutes or ten hours.

04:03.844 --> 04:05.813
The question is,
what turns this into a rape?

04:05.846 --> 04:07.681
- TARU said these texts went
to a burner?

04:07.715 --> 04:09.016
- Yeah.
- All right.

04:09.049 --> 04:11.519
So the victim,
Laura Collett, married,

04:11.552 --> 04:12.853
lives in Manhattan.
What else do we know?

04:12.886 --> 04:14.788
- She's 42.
She has one son.

04:14.822 --> 04:16.457
- And here's a screen shot
of her phone.

04:16.490 --> 04:17.458
- Just another perfect family.

04:17.491 --> 04:19.460
- Wow, it's just too early
to be that jaded.

04:19.493 --> 04:20.794
- Next time
I'll wait till noon.

04:20.828 --> 04:21.829
- The husband,
he's at the hospital?

04:21.862 --> 04:23.897
- Yeah, unis called.
- Great, head down there.

04:23.931 --> 04:25.933
See what he knows.

04:29.970 --> 04:31.605
- Excuse me.
Mr. Collett?

04:31.639 --> 04:33.507
I'm Detective Carisi.
This is Detective Rollins.

04:33.541 --> 04:34.608
- We're looking
into what happened

04:34.642 --> 04:36.844
with your wife last night.

04:36.877 --> 04:40.013
- You're investigating her
for overdosing on pills?

04:40.047 --> 04:42.015
- No, no, we're not.
We're trying to understand

04:42.049 --> 04:44.051
what happened prior to that.

04:44.084 --> 04:47.020
- Prior?
- Yeah.

04:47.054 --> 04:48.822
You see,
your wife sent a text message

04:48.856 --> 04:52.760
from her phone
accusing somebody of rape.

04:52.793 --> 04:57.698
- So she was at a hotel
with a man who raped her?

04:57.731 --> 05:01.034
- Right now, we're just trying
to figure out who she was with.

05:01.068 --> 05:02.936
- When was the last time
you talked to Laura?

05:02.970 --> 05:04.071
- Late afternoon.

05:04.104 --> 05:08.709
I was--my son and I were
in Boston, visiting colleges.

05:08.742 --> 05:10.611
- Did you know that she was
staying at the Luxembourg Hotel

05:10.644 --> 05:12.613
that night?

05:12.646 --> 05:15.616
Mr. Collett, do you have
any idea who Laura was with?

05:15.649 --> 05:17.485
Maybe with somebody from work?

05:17.518 --> 05:19.853
- No.
She doesn't work.

05:19.887 --> 05:21.989
She's involved with
various charities, but...

05:22.022 --> 05:25.859
- Okay.
- We were happy.

05:25.893 --> 05:29.730
At least I thought we were.
- Had she taken up anything new?

05:29.763 --> 05:32.065
Tennis, hiking, or yoga?

05:32.099 --> 05:34.502
- More like college admissions.

05:34.535 --> 05:35.836
That's all she thinks about,

05:35.869 --> 05:37.905
where my son will be going
to college next year.

05:37.938 --> 05:40.508
- Right.

05:40.541 --> 05:44.044
Well, look, Mr. Collett, we know
this is all overwhelming,

05:44.077 --> 05:46.514
but we'd like your consent
to do a rape kit.

05:46.547 --> 05:49.517
[solemn music]

05:49.550 --> 05:50.618
*

05:50.651 --> 05:51.619
- What do you got?

05:51.652 --> 05:53.721
- The hotel just sent over
security footage.

05:53.754 --> 05:55.088
All right, at 6:14 p.m.,

05:55.122 --> 05:56.657
Laura walks in
the hotel lobby.

05:56.690 --> 06:00.127
She says hello
to this tall, white man.

06:00.160 --> 06:02.530
Looks early 40s.
He's decent looking.

06:02.563 --> 06:03.597
Well-dressed.

06:03.631 --> 06:04.598
- I'll run it through
facial-rec.

06:04.632 --> 06:06.066
- Great, so meanwhile,
head back to that hotel,

06:06.099 --> 06:09.570
show that image to guests,
doormen, front desk.

06:09.603 --> 06:11.772
See if anybody knows
who this guy is.

06:11.805 --> 06:13.741
- All right, take a ride
to the Luxembourg Hotel?

06:13.774 --> 06:16.043
- No, I can't.

06:16.076 --> 06:19.647
Barba set up an interview with
me with some ADA in Brooklyn.

06:19.680 --> 06:20.881
- Brooklyn?

06:20.914 --> 06:23.784
You got to grow a beard and
start making artisan pickles?

06:23.817 --> 06:25.052
- I'm just seeing
what's out there, all right?

06:25.085 --> 06:28.656
For the record,
I like artisan pickles.

06:28.689 --> 06:31.559
- Mm.
- How do I look?

06:31.592 --> 06:33.594
- Like a cop.

06:35.763 --> 06:38.198
- Hey, how did Noah do?

06:38.231 --> 06:40.868
Okay, did you talk
to his teacher?

06:40.901 --> 06:43.003
Oh.

06:43.036 --> 06:46.106
Okay, thanks, Lucy.

06:46.139 --> 06:48.208
- Everything good
with the little guy?

06:48.241 --> 06:51.044
- Apparently,
Noah's language skills

06:51.078 --> 06:52.946
are slightly underdeveloped

06:52.980 --> 06:54.682
relative to his peer group.

06:54.715 --> 06:56.950
You know,
I've just been doing my best,

06:56.984 --> 06:59.653
you know,
reading and talking, singing--

06:59.687 --> 07:01.855
- So he's not getting
into the fancy school?

07:01.889 --> 07:04.825
- They don't know yet.

07:04.858 --> 07:06.694
Anything new
with Laura Collett?

07:06.727 --> 07:07.795
- Rape kit came back.

07:07.828 --> 07:11.064
No semen, bruises, or abrasions,
but she did have sex.

07:11.098 --> 07:13.601
They found traces
of condom lubricant.

07:13.634 --> 07:15.703
- Any facial-rec?
- No, the guy's still a ghost.

07:15.736 --> 07:17.838
- Anything on social media?
- No pops on the perp,

07:17.871 --> 07:19.740
but check this out.

07:19.773 --> 07:22.676
She DM'd her son the day
before the incident.

07:22.710 --> 07:24.144
- "I'm sorry.
Call me."

07:24.177 --> 07:25.846
- And he writes back,
"You make me sick.

07:25.879 --> 07:26.880
I hope you die."

07:26.914 --> 07:28.682
- Huh.

07:28.716 --> 07:30.884
- Those are pretty strong words.
- Yeah, maybe the kid found out

07:30.918 --> 07:31.952
his mother was seeing
somebody else.

07:31.985 --> 07:33.887
I'll go back to the hospital,
see what he knows.

07:33.921 --> 07:36.924
- How'd your meeting go
with LaRosa?

07:38.892 --> 07:40.894
What, you think
I don't hear things?

07:43.697 --> 07:46.199
[footsteps approaching]

07:49.670 --> 07:53.106
- Hey, Justin.
How's your mom?

07:53.140 --> 07:55.976
- She's still unconscious, but
the doctor sounds optimistic.

07:56.009 --> 07:57.044
- Good.

07:57.077 --> 07:58.111
- Not sure if
he really means it,

07:58.145 --> 08:00.280
or he's just trying
to placate me.

08:00.313 --> 08:02.683
- Placate, huh?
Nice.

08:02.716 --> 08:04.017
SAT word, right?

08:04.051 --> 08:05.018
- [laughs softly]

08:05.052 --> 08:08.789
- So listen, we got this
from the hotel security.

08:08.822 --> 08:12.693
Do you recognize this guy
with your mom?

08:12.726 --> 08:14.161
- No, sorry.

08:14.194 --> 08:16.196
- That's okay.

08:17.164 --> 08:19.700
[sighs]

08:19.733 --> 08:22.770
So listen, Justin.
I, um...

08:22.803 --> 08:24.237
I saw the message
you sent your mother

08:24.271 --> 08:26.940
the night of the incident.

08:26.974 --> 08:30.177
What was she so sorry about?

08:30.210 --> 08:32.846
Why did you say
that you wanted her to die?

08:32.880 --> 08:35.015
- She kept bugging me
about Hudson.

08:35.048 --> 08:39.787
She really wants me to go there.
She thinks it's so prestigious.

08:39.820 --> 08:43.123
- You know, my mother...

08:43.156 --> 08:44.958
[chuckles]

08:44.992 --> 08:48.061
My mother didn't even know
I applied to college.

08:48.095 --> 08:49.296
No, seriously.

08:49.329 --> 08:50.998
Two days before
classes started, I said,

08:51.031 --> 08:52.900
"Hey, Ma, can I borrow
400 bucks for books?

08:52.933 --> 08:54.301
I just got into St. John's."

08:54.334 --> 08:56.069
- Lucky you.

08:56.103 --> 08:58.071
My mom's been on
four campus tours of Hudson,

08:58.105 --> 08:59.840
sat in on six lectures,

08:59.873 --> 09:01.208
and had three lunches
with some guy

09:01.241 --> 09:03.310
from the admissions office.

09:03.343 --> 09:05.713
The other day, she asked me
to have lunch with him.

09:05.746 --> 09:07.915
Said he might be
the difference maker,

09:07.948 --> 09:09.717
and I snapped.

09:09.750 --> 09:11.852
I'm sick of dealing with
all her stress over all this.

09:11.885 --> 09:13.286
I'm the one applying.

09:13.320 --> 09:15.288
[solemn music]

09:15.322 --> 09:19.092
I just hope that's not the
last thing I ever said to her.

09:19.126 --> 09:23.096
